name: The Komoh Restaurant Bali
address: H6VC+522, Jl. I.GST. NGR Rai, Pangsan, Kec. Petang, Kabupaten Badung, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: Good restaurant to have lunch in Petang Badung. The local and Indonesian foods were delicious and affordable price. You can enjoy the rice field on the upper area with good view. The small river below you can reach through footpath they made.
review 2: We had to stop at this restaurant due to a strong storm. The ladies were really kind, and provided a great service. Nasi Goreng came with a meat skewer and it was delicious (great value). Highly recommended if you need a pit-stop.
review 3: We went there on our way to Nung Nung waterfall. The food was amazing and the owner and his family were so kind. Devinitly recommend this warung.
review 4: Very nice food! It was super cheap! Definitely go there if you are around. It‚Äôs close to the Nung nung waterfall !
review 5: A fantastic place to stop if using this route to head north. Big menu. Gado gado is excellent in my view.
